he power struggle he would later win against Derby’s son in the 1870s. Overall, it helps to provide us with a fuller picture of mid-Victorian Britain’s engagement with the world.This book will be of use to those teaching and studying Victorian politics and foreign policy at all levels in higher education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / General.2bisacsh  aBritish foreign policy.  aConservative Party.  aCrimean War.  aDisraeli.  aEarl of Derby.  aItalian Unification.  aNapoleon III.  agovernment.  ahigh politics.  amid-Victorian Britain.1 aHicks, Geoffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779147440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847791474423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847791474/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles